<title type="html"><![CDATA[Yet another reason to not use NESASM: Label length limit]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8116&amp;p=83988#p83988"><![CDATA[
I checked my NESASM code (two actual games), and longest label was 24 chars, unique enough far before it. Masochism is using labels that longer than 32 chars and first 32 chars are the same. If someone has labels that long and uniform, he needs better assembler for sure, with local labels and modules (i.e. local labels accessible through module and non-local label name, module.subroutine.internallabel).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Fri Sep 16, 2011 8:37 am</p><hr />
